SIMPLE: gravity
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gravity
<hw>Grav"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Gravities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>gravitas</ets>,
fr. <ets>gravis</ets> heavy; cf. F. <ets>gravit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Grave</er>, <pos>a.</pos>, <er>Grief</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of having weight; beaviness; <as>as, the <ex>gravity</ex>
of lead</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sobriety of character or demeanor.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Men
of <xex>gravity</xex> and learning.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 648 needs proofing ##proof - especially italicized words (also
in etymologies) are not properly marked --></p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Importance, significance, dignity, etc; hence,
seriousness; enormity; <as>as, the <ex>gravity</ex> of an
offense</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They derive an importance from . . . the <qex>gravity</qex> of the
place where they were uttered.</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>The tendency of a mass of
matter toward a center of attraction; esp., the tendency of a body
toward the center of the earth; terrestrial gravitation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Lowness of tone; -- opposed to
<contr>acuteness</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Center of gravity</b></col> <cd>See under
<er>Center</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Gravity battery</b></col>, <cd>See
<er>Battery</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 4.</cd> -- <col><b>Specific
gravity</b></col>, <cd>the ratio of the weight of a body to the weight
of an equal volume of some other body taken as the standard or unit.
This standard is usually water for solids and liquids, and air for
gases. Thus, 19, the specific gravity of gold, expresses the fact that,
bulk for bulk, gold is nineteen times as heavy as water.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gravy</ent>⟦br⟧
